==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quinoline
<hw>Quin"o*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Quin</ets>ine + L. <ets>ol</ets>eum oil +
<ets>-ine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A nitrogenous base,
<chform>C9H7N</chform> obtained as a pungent colorless liquid by the
distillation of alkaloids, bones, coal tar, etc. It the nucleus of many
organic bodies, especially of certain alkaloids and related substances;
hence, by extension, any one of the series of alkaloidal bases of which
quinoline proper is the type.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>chinoline</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quinologist</ent>⟦br⟧
